        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The military tracking data for March 11, 2026, reveals a range of activities across various domains. In the air, notable aircraft include transport and ISR platforms operating across the U.S. and internationally, indicating routine and specialized missions. The presence of training exercises suggests ongoing efforts to maintain readiness and proficiency. The naval intelligence highlights the deployment of the French aircraft carrier USS Charles De Gaulle in the Eastern Mediterranean and Red Sea, responding to regional tensions and Iranian drone attacks. The overall military posture indicates a focus on maintaining operational readiness, conducting training exercises, and responding to emerging threats in key regions. The strategic implications include a heightened state of alert and preparedness, particularly in response to potential conflicts and security challenges in the Middle East and other hotspots.</description>
